FFmpeg
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

sqz uses FFmpeg (ffmpeg, ffprobe) to inspect and re-encode media. It does NOT
bundle or redistribute FFmpeg. Instead, at the user's explicit request, the app
downloads a prebuilt FFmpeg into its own data folder, or uses FFmpeg binaries the
user already has on their system.

FFmpeg is a separate work with its own license. The prebuilt binaries sqz can
download are GPL-licensed builds. Those binaries are governed by their own
license (GPL); sqz's own source code remains under the MIT License.

  - FFmpeg is a trademark of Fabrice Bellard, originator of the FFmpeg project.
  - FFmpeg project & source: https://ffmpeg.org/  ·  https://git.ffmpeg.org/ffmpeg.git
  - Windows/Linux builds sqz downloads: https://github.com/BtbN/FFmpeg-Builds
  - macOS builds sqz downloads: https://evermeet.cx/ffmpeg/
